  • Class Summary
    Class
    Description
    BaseMutableWay
    Mutable way is the superclass of MutableWay and NewWay since both modifiable ways in the base may and new ways are both mutable and need to be treated the same with regards to tag modifications.
    ConnectionPoint
    Models a connection to a modified way at a particular location.
    MutableWay
    A class that holds an OSM way and models any changes that need to be made to nodes that are caused by adding new connections to the way (sometimes a connection can be made to an existing node and sometimes a new node needs to be added because there is no node reasonably close).
    NewWay
    Represents a new way being added to the base graph
    PbfNodeIdentifierList
    A list of PbfNodeIdentifiers.
    PbfTimestamp
    Represents a time in OSM style ISO format.
    RemovedWay
    Represents a way to remove
